LinkedHashMap
LinkedHashMap ek aisa Map hai jo insertion order maintain karta hai.
Matlab jo order me tum data daalte ho, wahi order me nikalta hai.

Internally:
HashMap + doubly linked list
Isliye order yaad rehta hai

Basic rules
Duplicate keys ❌
Values duplicate ho sakti hain ✅
Insertion order maintain hota hai ✅
1 null key allowed hai ✅
Time complexity ≈ O(1) (HashMap jaisa)

Ek line me samajh:
HashMap = fast but random order
TreeMap = sorted but slow
LinkedHashMap = fast + ordered (insertion)

